  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  consecutive cirrhotic patients undergoing TIPS

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  age &gt;75 years; bilirubin levels &gt;5 mg/dl; creatinine levels &gt;3 mg/dl; a serious
             cardiac or pulmonary dysfunction; a Child-Pugh's score &gt;11 (except for the patients
             candidates to early TIPS); a model end-stage liver disease (MELD) score &gt;18; a
             diagnosis of hepatic carcinoma; sepsis; spontaneous bacterial peritonitis; renal
             insufficiency. Present HE or previous spontaneous/recurrent HE, alcohol/psychoactive
             drugs intake (positive alcoholaemia and/or benzodiazepines or opioid urine
             metabolites) at the moment of evaluation, unrelated neurological disease including
             dementia (mini mental state &lt; 26).
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
